snippet.title: Celebrities Who Exposed Amber Heard Because Of Her Lie!!!
snippet.description:
Amber Heard was got caught lying. Do you think she should deserve second chance. These celebrities caught her lying. Find out more about watching the video.


Famous film and television actress Amber Heard is being called out for lying on numerous occasions by various celebrities. One such celebrity is her ex-husband and Golden Globe winner Johnny Depp. ‚ÄúThe Pirates of the Caribbean‚Äù actor who sees himself drawn towards controversies and legal battles had once filed a 50 million defamation case against ex-wife Amber Heard at the time of their divorce. According to sources, the defamation case has witnessed some recent happenings wherein Depp and his team has issued a legal notice to Amber Heard‚Äôs ex-boyfriend and one of the richest space enthusiasts in the world, Elon Musk.
1- One of these well-wishers is Vanessa Paradis, the former partner of Johnny Depp who was the first celebrity to openly support Depp and expressed her doubts regarding Amber‚Äôs allegations in May 2020 wherein she accused Johnny of being extremely violent. She even supported Depp‚Äôs defamation case against Heard by issuing a statement. In that statement, she claimed that she has known Johnny for 25 years and has never faced a problem with him. She also stated that Johnny has always been a reverent and caring partner to her and a doting father to their two children. Vanessa also went on to call Amber‚Äôs allegations against Depp to be completely false and baseless.
2- Winona Ryder too, another former partner of Johnny Depp came forward to publish a declaration in support of him in the matter. Ryder clarified that Amber has been unreasonable with her allegations and the Johnny that she has known for so many years, is not even one percent close to what Amber falsely described him as. Winona has always considered him as his closest friend, more like family and thus, she knows him better than anyone else. This would make her the perfect person to testify in favor of Johnny since she knows that he is innocent and far from being violent or abusive.

Johnny Depp fans have not wasted a single minute to come out in support of their favourite star as soon as this controversy came into limelight. His fans tweeted that they cannot wait for Depp to get justice and strict action to be taken against Amber. Not only the fans, even celebrities and colleagues have shown their support to Johnny Depp, implying that they know him personally and he has never had wrong intentions. During the two-year marriage of Depp and Heard, Depp was often shown in bad light by the media but his well-wishers knew better and never left his side.
3- Sharon Osbourne is a celebrity who is known to have no filters in her mouth and speaks her heart out without any hesitation and fear of judgement. In an interview in November 2020, Sharon suggested that according to her, Amber should have been scrutinized and blamed equally by the media for this entire situation as a marriage is supposed to be a two-way street. She believed that Amber should stop playing the victim card even though she was at fault in numerous situations. Sharon also drew a comparison between the relationship of Johnny and Amber and her relationship with her husband Ozzy Osbourne.

So, will Johnny be able to prove that Amber has been lying all this while or is it ultimately both of them who are responsible for this chaos equally? Only time will tell.
That‚Äôs all for today. I hope you liked the video. If you did make sure to hit that like button and subscribe to the channel so that you never miss any amazing video from us.

snippet.title: Brittany Murphy & Julia Davis - Organized Crime Victims (Border Control Whistleblowers)
snippet.description:
Brittany Murphy and Julia Davis were victims of organized crime to stop whistleblowing about border control... If you see someone getting targeted, say and do something publicly to support them to prevent ONE more Brittany Murphy.

Brittany Murphy died because she wrote/spoke up for & testified for Julia Davis. They tapped her and her husband's phones, surveilled her, caused them so much distress that she was prevented from working on Happy Feet.

Brittany Murphy and Department of Homeland Security Whistleblower Julia Davis were targeted victims. Davis was a stuntwoman on the movie set. Murphy lost her voice acting role for Happy Feet 2 when rumors spread that she was "paranoid" about helicopters, people following, monitoring, and wire tapping. This is purposeful victimization.

Brittany Murphy was killed with monitoring, simulated distress, then stimuli with trace toxins. They didn't screen right until her father did a private test. She died after showering from cardiac arrest in just her 30s. Her husband died shortly after.

The solution for victims is writing, interfering, reporting credibly, and seeing the patterns of targeting. The other side creates networks to isolate the victim.

- Victims Discredited, Organized Crime, and Border Control -

Julia Davis states nefarious entities want people to file reports to the police that people are following them in order to force evaluations. This discredits and victimizes them. There is absolutely no entity to report safely to when targeted, and all media will ignore them.

Brittany Murphy was found to have 10 metals at high levels in her body by an independent, non-governmental connected lab from Colorado. Her husband died of the same sudden effects 5 months later.

Circumstantial evidence points to Brittany Murphy and Simon Monjack being killed for being witnesses. Other whistleblowers have had relatives harmed, such as Kevin Ship.

Kevin Ship, a CIA Whistleblower, mentions, as does Julia Davis, that evaluations are done to discredit whistleblowers and people who are not being rescued. If not secrecy and persecution, then..

They were young. Brittany was 32 years old on December 20, 2009 when she died, and her husband Simon Monjack was 40 years old when he died May 23, 2010. How could young people have such weak immune systems to pass away from supposedly "pneumonia," and within 5 months of each other?

Labeling & coercion removes all survival instinct and ability to defend oneself against any harassment.

Brittany Murphy was not in a hospital before her sudden attack, and the scene of her quick interview at the end shows she was not "ill" enough to be in bed.
Her cardiac arrest was sudden, as was her death, and who would want to go to hospitals to see force?

Victimization by deception to discredit is real. Anyone targeted is not believed, and re-victimized. More force and coercion makes a person worse and nothing can be changed. Anyone who is a victim of a stalking crime, organized crime, or a toxin crime can be psych victimized.

Beliefs make people use force, which only reinforces victimization and perpetrators. It also removes people from work, due to their belief that people experiencing any hardship cannot handle a work or school schedule.

If you hear of a person victimized, try to stop the harassment, have them focus on goals, and expose the perpetrators.

Let the truth be known that Brittany Murphy and Julia Davis were targeted people.

(e.g., Ransom-Ware Claudestine Investigation Agency - law firms hire bad spies). 
*To be continued (always?)* 
Organized Crime is obsessed over border crossings, & often don't report to IRS.

2 - AH Case
"You should look at what Adam Waldman and the AI Bots do against Amber Heard - then how Rose McGowan tried to go onto AnonymousWorldwide recently, but never posted the audio, then had agents which stopped reporting by Journalists.... 
They always try to set up people with homeland, then that makes people have issues helping, so instead, they get help from the UK, which always has to clean up the messes.

Brittany Murphy's and Julia Davis's story (made a 2017 video on it) inspires me to interfere to prevent such another death from monitoring and set ups.... an ex staff partner 2 years ago sent a tweet saying they wanted to make lies about Amber's trips to the border (for Amnesty International/charity) and PIs...

snippet.title: Qatar airport hell: Why are the victims still waiting for answers? | 60 Minutes Australia
snippet.description:
Subscribe here: http://9Soci.al/chmP50wA97J Full Episodes: https://9now.app.link/uNP4qBkmN6 | The Deafening Silence (2021)

Exactly 12 months ago, reporter Sarah Abo interviewed one of the bravest women she'd ever met and told one of the most shocking stories she's ever reported. Jane was among 13 Australian women who'd been hauled off flights in the wealthy Persian Gulf state of Qatar and physically violated by airport authorities. It was disgraceful, completely unnecessary conduct that at the time was condemned around the world. Prime Minister Scott Morrison and Foreign Minister Marise Payne angrily vowed to get an explanation for how and why it happened. But a year on, you guessed it, Jane and the other victims have heard nothing. In fact, the silence is so deafening it's as if they didn't exist and their suffering never happened.

snippet.title: Survivors of White Island Disaster say they felt abandoned after eruption | 60 Minutes Australia
snippet.description:
Subscribe here: http://9Soci.al/chmP50wA97J Full Episodes: https://9now.app.link/uNP4qBkmN6 | White Island Volcano Disaster (2020)

It‚Äôs a terrible truth to have to acknowledge. The White Island volcano in New Zealand is not only spectacular but spectacularly dangerous. One awful afternoon last December, it erupted, seemingly without warning. Forty-seven tourists and guides, who up until the catastrophic explosion had only been thinking of adventure, were stranded on the island. All suffered injuries, and 21 died. Now, for the first time, Australian survivors talk about that tragic day and its devastating aftermath. They tell Sarah Abo it is a miracle that more people weren‚Äôt killed. But they also express their anger and ask questions about why they were allowed to visit such a perilous location in the first place, and why efforts to rescue them were flawed.

snippet.title: üîµChild Victim #2 | Nichiren Ogando Case | Police Interview
snippet.description:
A man is accused of using a hidden camera to secretly record his girlfriend and her children, according to the Coral Springs Police Department.

Interrogation has been redacted

Nichiren Rugeles Ogando, 37, allegedly used a camera disguised as a smoke detector to capture footage of them using the bathroom and taking a shower. One of the children is 7 years old and the other is 16 years old, police said.

Ogando‚Äôs girlfriend told investigators she ‚Äúdiscovered a smoke detector in her children‚Äôs bathroom,‚Äù which contained an SD card, according to the report. She told police she did not install the camera or give permission for it to be installed.

When police interrogated Ogando, he said he had never watched the videos. Detective weren‚Äôt buying it.

Investigators reportedly found 12 videos of his girlfriend, 32 videos of a 7 year old, and 65 videos of a 16 year old, undressing or using the bathroom on Ogando‚Äôs devices, the report states.

Ogando was arrested and is facing three counts of voyeurism.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp Victim Blames and ADMITS to Abuse / AUDIO
snippet.description:
This video is a clip which was excluded from the cut-up, edited and leaked recording by Johnny Depp‚Äôs team in January.  The full version was recorded by Johnny Depp and Amber Heard during their marriage (September 2015). The full recording is being used as evidence in the Johnny Depp v The Sun UK libel case. Depp decided to sue The Sun for publishing an article where they brand him a ‚Äòwife-beater‚Äô, for abusing his then wife, Amber Heard. 

When the cut-up/edited 46 minute version leaked in January by Depp‚Äôs team, it was made to portray a certain narrative and was used as propaganda. It was leaked 6 months before the trial began and used to lead people and potential jurors to believe that it was somehow an official piece of evidence, which it was not. It was incomplete.

If you‚Äôd like to read the official case documents, they can be found here: https://www.nickwallis.com/depp-trial

This recording was obtained through CourtTV and can be found here: https://www.courttv.com/news/amber-heard-witness-statements-depp-blamed-the-monster-for-physical-verbal-abuse/

You can listen to the FULL recording here: https://youtu.be/k9pbrBmHI58

Comments are disabled to combat abuse.

snippet.title: Amber Heard's Latest Plan of  Attack
snippet.description:
Amber Heard is reportedly going to London to testify against Johnny Depp in the Sun lawsuit trial.  She just might be shooting herself in the foot since testifying against Johnny Depp in court is breaking the NDA they both signed.  This has no bearing on the 7Mil she received from Johnny that she apparently donated to charity...that 7Mil was the legal settlement from the divorce since they did not have a prenup.  It was NOT a pay-off for her to stay silent despite what the Daily Mail article says about it.  Here is the article itself:

"Amber Heard will fly in to London next month to testify against ex-husband Johnny Depp over claims he beat her."
https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-8060735/Amber-Heard-fly-London-month-testify-against-ex-husband-Johnny-Depp.html

It's obvious to me that Amber is trying to break Johnny Depp down by showing up at court to testify.  Johnny has been there in London testifying
on his own, and if she shows up they might share a courtroom together.  That won't be pleasant for Johnny but this is what narcissists like Amber plan well.  She is trying to make Johnny fall apart and crumble at her feet.  He's not going to do that at this point, as far as I can see, but it's  pretty clear that she's banking on it.  After all, he didn't want to bring her down in 2016, he wanted to settle out so they could both come away unscathed.  He loved that woman deeply.  However, a lot can happen in four years and we're now in 2020.
Johnny Depp, I have no doubt, will stand his ground and show that these text messages were mere rants to a friend and not actual threats.  Amber was the abuser and he was the victim, but  he's not a victim any more.  He's fighting back and not leaving any stone unturned.

snippet.title: Victim or Perpetrator?
snippet.description:
Imagine you can hear a couple fighting, but you can‚Äôt see who‚Äôs raising their fists. Who‚Äôs in danger - the woman, or the man?

This is the question support worker Christine asks herself when she decides to make her female domestic abuse service available to male victims...and perpetrators. How can she distinguish the survivors from the abusers - while still offering a safe space for women?

"Victim or Perpetrator?" is the first full-length drama to explore domestic abuse in all its forms, across different ages - and across different genders.

Inspired by many real-life cases of abuse, the stories of people who've tried to help female & male victims, and the debate surrounding several celebrities (including Johnny Depp and Amber Heard)  - Secret Stories C.I.C presents a professionally recorded full-cast adaptation of the acclaimed 2019 stage play by Michael Beakhouse.

The radio drama is available to anyone who might find it useful via Spotify, Soundcloud and all major podcasting platforms.

Support for male survivors is available via Mankind Initiative (01823 334244), Both Parents Matter (0333 050 6815); and Break The Silence (www.breakthesilence.co.uk), who will also published Lee Marks' book "Break The Silence: A Support Guide For Male Victims Of Domestic Abuse" on 30th November 2021.

Support for female survivors is available via the National Domestic Abuse helpline (0808 2000 247), Women's Aid (https://www.womensaid.org.uk) and Refuge (0808 2000 247).

‚ÄúVictim or Perpetrator?‚Äù featured Peter Tavener as Jason and Derek Hogarth; Victoria Paterson as Christine, the Judge, and the Waitress; Belinda Duffy as Scarlet; and Michael Beakhouse as Alex. The play was recorded and mixed by Spriggan Productions.

snippet.title: Amberlynn Reid: "It's Not Fair" (The Victim Mentality)
snippet.description:
Amberlynn Reid's audience is often frustrated by her lack of accountability. She has a tendency to make excuses, blame other people and seemingly does not take responsibility for her actions - while simultaneously looking for sympathy.

This has lead to her being accused of possessing a "victim-mentality," even earning her the nickname "Victimlynn".

In this video we'll be discussing what the victim mentality is, where we can see it in Amberlynn Reid, and how it might be sabotaging any hope Amberlynn has at succeeding on her weight loss journey.

We cover Amberlynn Reid's general attitude toward her audience, the moment she quits Optavia, the "Binge Monster", 100 days of uploading, and most importantly the toxic mindset standing between Amberlynn and her health.

My hope is that with a greater understanding of the mindset and psychology of weight loss we all might be able to learn how to manage our weight and the obesity epidemic more effectively.

We all have a tendency to make excuses and rationalize away things we don't like - but ultimately the more we take ownership of our actions the more power we possess to change our behavior.

Thanks for watching - let me know if you have any suggestions for my future videos!

Song: Puddles - Stanley Gurvich
#AmberlynnReid #weightloss

snippet.title: Alec Baldwin Interview ABC Body Language Analysis on Rust Shooting of Halyna Hutchins
snippet.description:
Alec Baldwin says "I didn't pull the trigger". What do four of the world's top body language and behavior experts make of Alec Baldwin interview for ABC around the Rust shooting of Halyna Hutchins? Full ABC interview here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZOKpiWrUPUI

PLEASE SUBSCRIBE: https://www.youtube.com/thebehaviorpanel?sub_confirmation=1 
BUY BEHAVIOR PANEL MERCH: https://www.thebehaviorpanel.shop/ 

Alexander Baldwin is an American actor, writer, comedian, film producer, and political activist. He is the eldest of the four actor brothers in the Baldwin family. The actor said he did not pull the trigger and dispatch Hutchins, 42, and injured Souza, 48. The firearm he was holding, which Baldwin believed to be safe, went off during rehearsals for the western. This action was not in the Rust script. The incident shocked Hollywood and prompted a reckoning over production safety and the use of weapons on set. Baldwin responded to comments by fellow actors, such as George Clooney, who said they checked weapons themselves, saying: ‚ÄúThere were a lot of people who felt it necessary to contribute some comment to the situation" "My protocol was to trust the person that had the job.‚Äù

The Behavior Panel is a group made up of the world's top body language and behavior experts, Mark Bowden, Scott Rouse, Greg Hartley, and Chase Hughes. Together they analyze the body language and behavior displayed in videos in the public interest. The Behavior Panel is a non-partisan group, looking to educate and entertain the public with their interest and expertise in nonverbal communication, body language, deception detection, interrogation, and resistance to interrogation. By looking at the gestures, facial expressions, micro-expressions, and context around what people say, this group of nonverbal behavior experts reveals the possible truth and deceptions. This behavior profiler group takes on the task of investigating the behavior behind the crime news that often forces us to think and feel the way we do. The Behavior Panel is a task force made up of four of the best body language and behavior profiler experts in the world.

Baldwin responded to comments by fellow actors, such as George Clooney, who said they checked weapons themselves, saying: ‚ÄúThere were a lot of people who felt it necessary to contribute some comment to the situation" "My protocol was to trust the person that had the job.‚Äù

The Behavior Panel is a group made up of the world's top body language and behavior experts, Mark Bowden, Scott Rouse, Greg Hartley, and Chase Hughes. Together they analyze the body language and behavior displayed in videos in the public interest. The Behavior Panel is a non-partisan group, looking to educate and entertain the public with their interest and expertise in nonverbal communication, body language, deception detection, interrogation, and resistance to interrogation. By looking at the gestures, facial expressions, micro-expressions, and context around what people say, this group of nonverbal behavior experts reveals the possible truth and deceptions. This behavior profiler group takes on the task of investigating the behavior behind the crime news that often forces us to think and feel the way we do. The Behavior Panel is a task force made up of four of the best body language and behavior profiler experts in the world.

The case could be dropped, due to public prosecution. I'm appalled at kj's coverage, she is causing way more harm than she is even aware of. This is why the code of ethics exists and Katie is going against everything, set in place to protect the victims and the public from being further traumatised! I call for a woacb black out.

2:08 My opinions are heavily formed from my past work for child protection & being a CSA survivor myself.

This is the big picture of the harm kj is causing. 
9:15 Katie's IG post that set me off, I shared it on twitter but I won't be reading out the CSA she details.

15:44 A lot of Katie's followers are from the special needs groups & / have special needs, these people are already vulnerable & the unnecessary details are going to affect her audience on a grand scale, imo.

- I said 'spiteful' instead of 'spiritual', in the last sentence, apologies for that. 
20:55 Amber Portwood is that you? Nope it's Katie 'lacking emotional intelligence' Paulson, forcing herself to show emotion, yet all we see is a desperate attempt & crocodile tears.. 
25:57 Calling for a community blackout, regarding kj's coverage of JD's trial. Katie gets a buzz from audiences reaction to her coverage. Don't give her that. Also, don't share her shit. Take a week off, stand with the victims, let's make sure that Katie doesn't jeopardise this case!!!
31:56 I even tagged instagram in my tweet.. I've reported all her ig posts & I'm not telling you to do this but you should consider reporting her posts if you feel she has crossed certain boundaries. Katie will never learn, if the platforms she posts on do not start holding her accountable! Ffs! 
32:52 Someone who enjoys the details of CSA, should not be covering a CSA trial! I know detectives that are scarred by details of CSA, no one wants to know these details, no one I have ever come across irl, working in child protection & tracking predators online, never have I come across anyone willing to verbalise CSA details to an audience who are the general public..real journalists have a responsibility to minimise harm

snippet.title: MEN ARE VICTIMS OF DOMESTIC VIOLENCE TOO
snippet.description:
Hey guys, so some people have asked me to do a part 2 to my previous chatty video, this is as close as it will get to one unfortunately as I don't think I need to say anymore on the actual Johnny Depp/Amber Heard divorce case, I have done this one because people have asked questions about my fathers situation and I felt I needed to go into more detail as a lot of people still don't understand domestic violence, let alone, domestic violence against men. 

I have used Johnny Depp as an example of seeing signs only in this video, there were never any allegations made against Amber Heard from him or his team, but the signs I saw in him are of emotional abuse. 

There have been statements to say that she was aggressive towards him on multiple occasions, you can find them by looking for them on Google.

Emma Roberts abused Evan Peters, link - http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2366343/Emma-Roberts-arrested-domestic-violence-boyfriend-Evan-Peters-leaving-actor-bloody-nose-bite-mark.html

Sorry for the depressing video, but Domestic Violence is a taboo topic not discussed enough, especially when it is against men.

Over 40% of DV victims are male, most shelters are female orientated and men do not get the same help as women do. 

If you're approached by a male victim, or if there is something that you CAN do to help someone, please do help them, take them just as seriously as you would a woman, because abuse is not confined to just one gender.

And please, be respectful when commenting, whether you agree with what I say or not, I am still a human, and I still have someone in this awful situation. Hurtful, disgusting comments will be reported and removed. 

Thank you so much to everyone for your support on the last video, I can't believe how ultimately positive the response was.

If anybody is in this situation and you need to talk, i'm on twitter and instagram: 

T: @burnttautumn
I: @autumonvenus

I hope you all had a lovely Christmas. 

xoxo

Sorry for the depressing video, but Domestic Violence is a taboo topic not discussed enough, especially when it is against men.

Over 40% of DV victims are male, most shelters are female orientated and men do not get the same help as women do. 

If you're approached by a male victim, or if there is something that you CAN do to help someone, please do help them, take them just as seriously as you would a woman, because abuse is not confined to just one gender.

And please, be respectful when commenting, whether you agree with what I say or not, I am still a human, and I still have someone in this awful situation. Hurtful, disgusting comments will be reported and removed. 

Thank you so much to everyone for your support on the last video, I can't believe how ultimately positive the response was.

If anybody is in this situation and you need to talk, i'm on twitter and instagram: 

T: @burnttautumn
I: @autumonvenus

I hope you all had a lovely Christmas. 

xoxo

Subscribe here: http://9Soci.al/chmP50wA97J Full Episodes: https://9now.app.link/uNP4qBkmN6 | Terminal Hell (2020)

Qatar is a small but wealthy country in the Persian Gulf. It promotes itself as a modern and progressive state that welcomes and respects foreign visitors. But that‚Äôs far from the truth. In reality Qatar is a dangerous destination, especially for western women. Even transiting through its international airport is risky. As Sarah Abo reports, the problem is a culture of entrenched misogyny, which seven weeks ago resulted in an appalling incident where a large group of women, including 13 Australians, were snatched off flights and physically violated by Qatari authorities. For the first time one of the victims, a brave young woman from Victoria, tells of her nightmare at Doha International Airport. And the story of how she was assaulted is so unbelievable that not only will it outrage all Australians, it‚Äôs sure to make people reassess future travel to or via Qatar.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp ADMITS To His Aggressive Temper and Victim Blames Amber Heard / EXCLUSIVE
snippet.description:
Hi there! This video is a clip which was excluded from the cut-up, edited and leaked recording by Johnny Depp‚Äôs team in January.  The full version was recorded by Johnny Depp and Amber Heard during their marriage (September 2015). The full recording is being used as evidence in the Johnny Depp v The Sun UK libel case. Depp decided to sue The Sun for publishing an article where they brand him a ‚Äòwife-beater‚Äô, for abusing his then wife, Amber Heard. 

When the cut-up/edited 46 minute version leaked in January by Depp‚Äôs team, it was made to portray a certain narrative and was used as propaganda. It was leaked 6 months before the trial began and used to lead people and potential jurors to believe that it was somehow an official piece of evidence, which it was not. It was incomplete.

If you‚Äôd like to read the official case documents, they can be found here: https://www.nickwallis.com/depp-trial

This recording was obtained through CourtTV and can be found here: https://www.courttv.com/news/amber-heard-witness-statements-depp-blamed-the-monster-for-physical-verbal-abuse/

You can listen to the FULL recording here: https://youtu.be/k9pbrBmHI58

Comments are disabled to combat abuse.

Amber Heard‚Äôs fate in ‚ÄòAquaman 2‚Äô remains uncertain amid Johnny Depp‚Äôs defamation case
https://micky.com.au/amber-heards-fate-in-aquaman-2-remains-uncertain-amid-johnny-depps-defamation-case/

Amber Heard may no longer reprise her role as Mera in Aquaman 2. Speculations regarding the actress‚Äô rumored firing became rife after an audiotape where she admitted to abusing her ex-husband, Johnny Depp made headlines.

In the lengthy clip, Heard and Depp are engaging in a heated argument. Heard taunts the Pirates of the Caribbean star and tells him that no one would believe that he‚Äôs a victim of domestic violence. As of late, the heads at DC have not yet revealed their decision when it comes to Heard. But there are rumors that Heard‚Äôs screen time in Aquaman 2 will become limited if she continues to appear in the sequel.

Tom King Teases 'Insanely Ambitious' Unannounced Project
https://www.cbr.com/tom-king-unannounced-project/

Tom King has announced that he's nearly finished a new limited series, which, according to him, is one of the most ambitious projects he's ever worked on.

Tom King offered no details about the project; it remains to be seen if this is a project with DC Comics or a creator-owned project he is developing. He has, however, teased a Watchmen project multiple times.

Female-Focused ‚ÄòStar Wars‚Äô Series From ‚ÄòRussian Doll‚Äôs‚Äô Leslye Headland In Works At Disney+
https://deadline.com/2020/04/new-star-wars-series-female-led-leslye-headland-russian-doll-disney-plus-1202915221/

Disney+ is developing a female-centered Star Wars series that will be written and showrun by Lesley Headland, a co-creator of Netflix‚Äôs Emmy-winning dramedy series Russian Doll.

It marks the latest Disney+ original series in the Star Wars universe, following the successful The Mandalorian created by Jon Favreau which is already underway on Season 3 ahead of its Season 2 bow. That too has a strong female element in Gina Carano‚Äôs butt-kicking shock trooper-turned-mercenary Cara Dune.

Twitter 'Cancels' Adam Driver
https://www.cbr.com/twitter-cancels-adam-driver-with-new-hashtag/

Some Twitter users are trying to "cancel" Star Wars' Kylo Ren actor Adam Driver. The hashtag began trending on April 20, apparently in response to a 2019 New Yorker interview in which Driver talked about how, at the age of 18, he joined the Marines after the Sep. 11 terrorist attacks. Adam Driver was medically discharged from the Marines and later enrolled in The Julliard School. 

DC Comics' Batman to Continue in June
https://www.cbr.com/batman-92-june-james-tynion-iv/

Batman writer James Tynion IV has revealed when Batman #92 will hit shelves as DC attempts to go back to normal amid the industry shutdown.

With DC Comics' physical releases being put on hold as a result of the industry-wide shutdown stemming from the Coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic, one title that has been of particular interest is Batman #92 -- which was originally scheduled for release on April 1. Batman series writer James Tynion IV has now confirmed the new issue is set to arrive sometime this June.

DC Expands Digital First, New Titles Arriving Daily
https://www.cbr.com/dc-digital-first-essential-reads-expansion/

DC has announced it's expanding its DC Digital First publishing program, with a number of new titles arriving daily.

The titles arriving during the first week of the expansion, previously exclusive to the DC Giants, include Superman: The Man of Tomorrow, by Robert Venditti, Batman: Gotham Nights, featuring a story by Brad Meltzer, Jim Lee, and Alex Sinclair with a second story by Larry Hama, and Wonder Woman: Agent of Peace, by Amanda Conner and Jimmy Palmiotti.

#amberheard #starwars #AdamDriverIsOverParty

Email wesdigscomics@gmail.com

snippet.title: Serial Killer Sunday - Bobby Joe Long
snippet.description:
#truecrime  #coldcase   #serialkiller #bobbyjoelong

"Robert Joseph Long (October 14, 1953 ‚Äì May 23, 2019), also known as Bobby Joe Long, was an American serial killer and rapist who was executed by the state of Florida for the murder of Michelle Denise Simms.[1] Long abducted, sexually assaulted, and murdered at least 10 women in the Tampa Bay Area in Florida during an eight-month period in 1984. He released one of his last victims, 17-year-old Lisa McVey, after raping her over a period of 26 hours. McVey provided critical information to the police that enabled them to arrest Long. Long was sentenced to death for two of the ten murders. He was executed by lethal injection on May 23, 2019." -wikipedia

snippet.title: Pregnant librarian shot dead on her street; Off-duty cop charged with taking a body home - TCDPOD
snippet.description:
This week on True Crime Daily The Podcast: A librarian in Florida is accused of bumping a motorcyclist in traffic in a road-rage incident. The pregnant woman is followed home by the rider and other witnesses before she's shot dead in the street after reportedly getting a gun from her house (2:13). No one is charged in the case.
And a New Jersey cop is arrested after allegedly killing a pedestrian in a traffic crash, leaving the scene, then returning to retrieve the victim's body, bringing it home to mom's house, then bringing the body back, where police arrest him at the scene (28:38). He and his mother and a passenger are facing charges.
Attorney Phillip C. Hamilton joins host Ana Garcia.

snippet.title: Alleged rape victim 'horrified' after death of photographer David Hamilton (Live News)
snippet.description:
The movie, based on a Martin Amis novel, was removed from a film festival and has been stuck in legal purgatory ever since.

Amber Heard is facing a $10m (¬£8m) lawsuit for "breach of performance and promotional obligations" in her latest film London Fields.

The actress is said to have "falsely claimed" she had "not agreed to the use of nude and simulated sex scenes", among other accusations.

This is the latest in a string of legal cases surrounding the unreleased film.

It comes after director Mathew Cullen sued the film's producers for fraud, claiming they hijacked the final cut of the movie.

The producers hit back with a counterclaim, accusing Cullen of failing to deliver the film on budget and on time.

London Fields, based on Martin Amis' celebrated novel, was supposed to premiere last year at the Toronto Film Festival.

But despite high anticipation, the film got stuck in legal purgatory without a distributor.

Now, Heard is facing claims of breaching contract and "committing tortious interference".

The complaint, filed in Los Angeles Superior Court, blames Heard for "hijacking the film" and "placing it under a limbo".

"While the inherent tension between actors and directors (on the one hand) and producers (on the other) is nothing new in Hollywood, the unauthorised and unlawful acts of Heard, Cullen, and others - most notably, their campaign to damage Plaintiff, the Picture, and the Picture's investors - are perhaps unprecedented," it reads.

It states Heard disregarded contractual obligations by failing to promote the movie.

Adding to the intrigue are rumours that the film played a part on the actress' divorce from Johnny Depp.

Depp, who makes a cameo in the film, was accused by Heard of having written the name of co-star Billy Bob Thornton in blood in the couple's bathroom wall.

London Fields stars Thornton as Samson Young, a terminally ill writer who has suffered from writer's block for twenty years, and femme fatale Amber Heard, stuck in the middle of a love triangle.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp says he's victim of 'elaborate hoax' amid Amber Heard claims
snippet.description: Johnny Depp's legal battle continued at London's High Court today. ¬†Depp, 57, is suing News Group Newspapers for libel over a story published in The Sun in 2018 which branded him a "wife beater" - a claim which he strenuously denies. ¬†Sasha Wass, QC, for NGN, said today that Depp respected 'limited responsibility' for his behaviour insisting that he `does kick and punch property but does not kick and punch people'. ¬†Wass said it was only a `small step' to transfer that anger to people. ¬†Any distinction was `meaningless' when Depp was so intoxicated during these episodes 'he would not have known what he was doing'.   ¬†Wass says Depp's wife-beating was over a three-year period from 2013 and 2016 while Depp claims he is the victim of an `elaborate hoax'. ¬†The actor alleges ex Amber Heard and her friends 'painted on injuries, manipulated photographs and destroyed property'. ¬†Wass said that would have meant Heard indulged in a `pre-planned conspiracy over her entire relationship' with Depp.   ¬†Depp denied he ever assaulted Heard, and accused her of being the violent party and reversed his role with hers. ¬†Wass said Depp's `PR machine' had `kicked in' to support his claim.  ¬†Though Heard was arrested for domestic abuse no charges were brought and Tasya Van Ree - the alleged victim - has denied any offence took place. ¬†Wass told the court that Depp is a "hopeless addict who repeatedly lost control". ¬†She also addressed his claims that Heard was the aggressor in the relationship, insisting that Heard at eight stone (115lb) was physically unable to attack him or fight him off.
snippet.tags: ['More OnJohnny Depp', 'Amber Heard']

snippet.title: Amber Heard Admits To Johnny Depp That She Can't Control Herself
snippet.description:
Amber Heard is an abuser. She is a manipulator. She is a liar. She was arrested for assaulting her partner before Johnny, and she should be in prison right now for what she did to him.

After she chopped off part of Depp's finger, which thankfully they were able to reattach, he got MRSA twice and was in serious danger. It is really sad the way society turns a blind eye to male victims of domestic abuse.

I'm disgusted to find out that she is getting additional screen time as Mera in the Justice League Snyder Cut. She shouldn't be portrayed in films as some sort of hero for young girls to look up to. She shouldn't be in films at all. She should be in jail.

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

"You can please tell people that it was a fair fight, and see what the jury and judge thinks. Tell the world, Johnny, tell them Johnny Depp, I Johnny Depp, a man, I'm a victim too of domestic violence.. and see how many people believe or side with you."
-Amber Heard

#JusticeForJohnnyDepp

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

1 in 4 men have been physically assaulted by an intimate partner at least once in their lifetimes (slapped, shoved, etc).
(Approximately 40 million men)

1 in 7 men have been SEVERELY attacked by an intimate partner at least once in their lifetimes (shot, stabbed, burned, choked, etc).
(Approximately 23 million men)

Nearly half of all men have experienced psychological abuse from an intimate partner (threats, stalking, manipulation, humiliation, economic exploitation, etc).

(USA numbers) Male domestic abuse goes mostly unreported because of the social stigma attached to it, but it's almost a certainty that you know at least one man who has been a victim of it. Crime knows no gender.

This video answers the questions: Can I analyze the mental health and personality factors at play in the Jussie Smollett case? What about his claim of innocence?
Support Dr. Grande on Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/drgrande

Narcissism:

There are two types of narcissism: With grandiose narcissism we see characteristics like being extroverted, socially bold, self-confident, having a superficial charm, being resistant to criticism, and being callous and unemotional. Vulnerable narcissism is characterized by shame, anger, aggression, hypersensitivity, a tendency to be introverted, defensive, avoidant, anxious, depressed, socially awkward, and shy.

snippet.title: Amber Heard & Johnny Depp Talk The ‚ÄòMONSTER‚Äô / AUDIO
snippet.description:
This video is a clip which was excluded from the cut-up, edited and leaked recording by Johnny Depp‚Äôs team in January.  The full version was recorded by Johnny Depp and Amber Heard during their marriage (September 2015). The full recording is being used as evidence in the Johnny Depp v The Sun UK libel case. Depp decided to sue The Sun for publishing an article where they brand him a ‚Äòwife-beater‚Äô, for abusing his then wife, Amber Heard. 

When the cut-up/edited 46 minute version leaked in January by Depp‚Äôs team, it was made to portray a certain narrative and was used as propaganda. It was leaked 6 months before the trial began and used to lead people and potential jurors to believe that it was somehow an official piece of evidence, which it was not. It was incomplete.

If you‚Äôd like to read the official case documents, they can be found here: https://www.nickwallis.com/depp-trial

This recording was obtained through CourtTV and can be found here: https://www.courttv.com/news/amber-heard-witness-statements-depp-blamed-the-monster-for-physical-verbal-abuse/

You can listen to the FULL recording here: https://youtu.be/k9pbrBmHI58

Comments are disabled to combat abuse.

snippet.title: PROOF Johnny Depp CONTROLLED Amber Heard / AUDIO
snippet.description:
This video is a clip which was excluded from the cut-up, edited and leaked recording by Johnny Depp‚Äôs team in January.  The full version was recorded by Johnny Depp and Amber Heard during their marriage (September 2015). The full recording is being used as evidence in the Johnny Depp v The Sun UK libel case. Depp decided to sue The Sun for publishing an article where they brand him a ‚Äòwife-beater‚Äô, for abusing his then wife, Amber Heard. 

When the cut-up/edited 46 minute version leaked in January by Depp‚Äôs team, it was made to portray a certain narrative and was used as propaganda. It was leaked 6 months before the trial began and used to lead people and potential jurors to believe that it was somehow an official piece of evidence, which it was not. It was incomplete.

If you‚Äôd like to read the official case documents, they can be found here: https://www.nickwallis.com/depp-trial

This recording was obtained through CourtTV and can be found here: https://www.courttv.com/news/amber-heard-witness-statements-depp-blamed-the-monster-for-physical-verbal-abuse/

You can listen to the FULL recording here: https://youtu.be/k9pbrBmHI58

Comments are disabled to combat abuse.

snippet.title: Safeguarding & Child Protection Webinar Recording
snippet.description:
The Stop the Violence team is pleased to invite member organisations to a virtual workshop on safeguarding and child protection as part of 16 Days of Activism.

Safeguarding is an action or series of actions taken to protect children from harm. Child protection is a part of safeguarding. This webinar workshop will include expert speakers and provide practical examples of how to create a strong policy within your guiding organisation.

The webinar was aimed at leaders of member organisations that currently do not have a safeguarding policy or wish to know how to strengthen an existing policy and to give leaders the confidence to know how they can support a child who is being harmed or is at risk of being harmed.

Speakers:
Coralie Mercier
Coralie has been working in the humanitarian sector for over 12 years. Throughout this time, she has worked as Program Manager, Field Manager, Deputy head of Mission in Asia, Africa, Europe, Middle East and South America. she has participated actively in coordination in protracted, sudden onset and complex emergencies. She has worked in both natural disaster and conflict settings working with IDP‚Äôs, refugees and host communities. Since 2018, she has worked as a Safeguarding specialist for three international NGOs. She has supported 3 HQ offices, 8 network head offices and 59 field operations with the implementation of risk-reduction and abuse-handling measures as set out in the Code of Conduct, in the policy on the Protection against sexual exploitation, abuse and harassment (PSEAH) and in the Child Protection policy.

Ariadna Bonomi
Ariadna has been working for the Ministry of Social Development of Argentina for 11 years. She works with people who have suffered gender violence, members of the LGBTIQ + collective and people in situations of social vulnerability. In her Association, Asociaci√≥n Gu√≠as Argentinas, she served as Head of Relations with the Society until October of this year. Currently, she is the head the Diversity and Gender Committee of my Association and I am working on setting up an Accompaniment Committee to give advice in cases of child abuse or violence.
snippet.channelTitle: World Association of Girl Guides and Girl Scouts

snippet.title: The Sextortion of Amanda Todd - the fifth estate
snippet.description:
A year after her death, most people remember Amanda Todd from her YouTube video, holding up hand-written pages describing how one mistake in front of a webcam led to her torment by bullies at school and online.  But beyond that viral video, the fifth estate reveals a more complex and disturbing story about what happened to the B.C. teenager driven to suicide in October 2012 ‚Äì not just bullying, but the deliberate sexual extortion of a 15-year-old girl by online predators.  the fifth estate host Mark Kelley goes deep into Amanda‚Äôs world, with never-before-seen videos and web chats from two personal laptops that her family shared with the fifth estate. With in-depth interviews from her mother, father and friends, Kelley reveals the untold story of The Sextortion of Amanda Todd.

Original Airdate : November 15th, 2013

For more on the fifth estate : http://www.cbc.ca/fifth

snippet.title: Amber Heard - SHIELD Act -  Congresswoman Jackie Speier - Stop Online Photo Abuse
snippet.description:
Stop Online Photo Abuse/#RevengePorn - Amber Heard's Speech with Congresswoman Jackie Speier (D-CA). SHIELD is federal legislation that targets perpetrators who knowingly share sexually explicit or nude images of someone without OBTAINING ANY consent. 
Amber Heard is a victim of hacks in 2014 which released her photos for harassment and manipulation.

The SHIELD (stopping Harmful Image Exploitation and Limiting Distribution) Act will hold accountable and deter violators of intimate privacy...

‚ÄúFor victims of nonconsensual pornography, #technology today makes it possible to destroy a person‚Äôs life with the click of a button or a tap on a cell phone. The damage caused by these attacks can crush careers, tear apart families, and, in the worst cases, has led to suicide,‚Äù Rep. Speier said. 

‚ÄúWhat makes these acts even more despicable is that many predators have gleefully acknowledged that the vast majority of their victims have no way of fighting back...‚Äù

‚ÄúSAG-AFTRA represents 160,000 actors, singers, dancers, broadcasters and recording artists who are at high risk of being victimized by image-based sexual abuse,‚Äù said David White, the National Executive Director of the Screen Actors Guild ‚Äì American Federation of Television and Radio Artists."

In Worldie's view, sometimes people don't have to time to say no or to not give consent when it's online harassment done with croudsourced hate. Just like in-person, you should not be able to harass, threaten, or incite violence online. 

It's not speech - it's hostile work environment. 

It's time to remove the Online "Wild West" - victims often don't fit high social credit ratings, do they?

WHO:
Congresswoman Jackie Speier (D-CA), Co-Chair, Democratic Women‚Äôs Caucus
Congressman John Katko (R-NY)
Amber Heard, Actor and Privacy Rights Advocate
Katelyn Bowden, Founder, The BADASS Army
David White, National Executive Director, SAG-AFTRA
Mary Anne Franks, Professor of Law, University of Miami School of Law, and President and Legislative & Tech Policy Director, Cyber Civil Rights Initiative
Holly Jacobs, Founder, Board Member, Cyber Civil Rights Initiative

snippet.title: Amber Heard's Lawyer EXPOSES Her For Ruining Johnny Depp's LIFE!!
snippet.description:
Amber Heard's Lawyer EXPOSES Her For Ruining Johnny Depp's LIFE!!

Subscribe to The Spotlight üëâ  https://bit.ly/3txAgy1

WATCH NEXT: ‚ñ∂Ô∏è

RELATED VIDEOS:üëá

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pZR2_v4UpgI&t=2s

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O1Rrb3ET21c

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iT2Kiyt7-rk


Heard used to act in well-directed independent movies and gained fame but her actual turning point was her portrayal of Queen Mera in Justice League which she went ahead with, in the Aquaman movie also. 

It was one of the highest-grossing films in 2018 and she gained international recognition because of that role. She even was nominated as a global spokesperson for L'Oreal Paris. She even dated Elon Musk for a year until early 2018!

Amber Heard had things going good for her until the controversy struck and her whole career braked to a halt over allegations that she abused Depp and he was the victim of abuse during their marriage.

The entirety of Hollywood was split into two, one favoring her and one favoring her ex-husband during this scandal. When she stepped out as a victim of marital abuse, she got a lot of support and concern from all fans. 

Sympathy went to Depp and most of the production houses didn't want any of them to be broiled in controversy after casting. Heard lost her role in Aquaman 2 and expressed her deep disappointment and Depp stepped down from his role as Grindelwald in the Crimes of Grindelwald movie of the Fantastic Beasts franchise. 

Johnny Depp was first married to Lori Allison and later got engaged to Jennifer Grey but finally proposed to Winona Ryder who was his co-star. He was so obsessed with her, he tattooed ‚ÄúWinona Forever‚Äù on his right arm. 

But that didn‚Äôt work out and he instead hit it up with Vanessa Paradis and has two children with her. Paradise and he separated in 2012 and then walked Amber Heard into his life.

Amber Heard was dating Tasya van Ree in the 2010s and they broke up in 2011. There was a charge against her for misdemeanor and domestic violence, but Ree later said that it was just over-sensationalized.Heard met Depp in 2012 on the sets of a movie and they dated and even lived together for three years. They then got married in 2015. 

Within 7 months, in 2016, they filed for divorce. But it wasn‚Äôt just divorce, she pressed charges against him for verbal and physical abuse under alcohol influence. 

Heard went ahead to release pictures and evidence of her abuse which garnered more outrage. They alleged that their relationship was passionate and volatile but forever bound by love. They said that they did not do this for the money and yet, Johnny Depp had to pay Heard an amount of 7 million US dollars, which she donated to the Children's Hospital in Los Angeles.

Fans thought that was it, everything had settled, but Heard published an op-ed in the Washington Post where the narrative was about her as an abuse victim. It did not mention Depp in any way, yet he took action and slapped a libel case on her. In a huge twist, he accused Heard of physical abuse, provided evidence, and said that all her claims were a hoax.

This was all that Depp wanted, he started to sue all the articles that labeled him a ‚Äúwife-beater‚Äù and other claims but the High Court of Justice voted in Heard‚Äôs favor and said that his claims of the whole thing being a hoax was not justified. Depp decided to appeal the decision and in order to give his all for it, decided to step down from his role in Crimes of Grindelwald and was replaced by Mads Mikkelsen. Boycott Amber heard

After the call by the actor to contest Heard's claim, fans showed massive response by flooding Twitter with DeppMovieNight and Deppcember where they organized a 24-hour movie marathon to show WeStandWithJohnnyDepp.

Due to their massive activism in Depp's aspect, they generated an online petition to get Heard removed from Aquaman 2 which succeeded and she was very heartbroken about it. Such was the huge controversy in Johnny Depp's life. 

The mic drop comes because Amber Heard's lawyers quit. This was quite the turnaround as at this crucial junction it is unheard of for lawyers of great distinction to quit. Roberta Kaplan is a high-profile lawyer and her withdrawal from the case and letting Heard take up the services of another counsel called Elaine Bredehoft from Virginia is quite shocking. Depp seems to be moving on and has the case to persist in the case. Depp's defamation lawsuit against Heard will be commenced in the spring of 2021.  clevver news  johnny depp amber heard  amber heard aquaman 2

snippet.title: Amber Heard requests ex Johnny Depp submit to mental health evaluation  - Fox News
snippet.description:
Thanks for watching my video. 
If you like my videos, please subscribe to the channel to receive the latest videos 
Videos can use content-based copyright law contains reasonable use Fair Use (https://www.youtube.com/yt/copyright/). 
For any copyright, please send me a message.  ¬†Amber Heard has officially requested ex-husband Johnny Depp submit to a mental health assessment, according to new court documents. ¬†Legal docs obtained by The Blast indicate the world‚Äôs third most beautiful woman is asking that a mental health professional be allowed to run an Independent Mental Evaluation ‚Äî or IME ‚Äî on the ‚ÄúPirates of the Caribbean‚Äù actor. Heard believes Johnny‚Äôs alleged drug, alcohol and prescription med usage contributed to his alleged abuse. ¬†‚ÄúJohnny‚Äôs relationship with reality oscillates, depending upon his interaction with alcohol and drugs,‚Äù reads the court doc. ‚ÄúAs Johnny‚Äôs paranoia, delusions and aggression increased throughout our relationship, so has my awareness of his continued substance abuse.‚Äù ¬†Depp¬†filed a $50 million defamation lawsuit in Virginia last year¬†after Heard ‚Äì his wife for just over a year until they separated in May 2016 ‚Äì penned a Washington Post op-ed about¬†her experience as a victim of domestic violence. While Depp was not named in the piece, he insisted it was strongly inferred he was the perpetrator. Heard responded by detailing the ‚Äúhorrific‚Äù abuse she allegedly suffered at his hands. ¬†Johnny‚Äôs attorney responded to the IME request saying it makes no sense to run a test today when the couple‚Äôs past is what‚Äôs in question. ¬†‚ÄúThis is a defamation case in which Mr. Depp does not allege that he suffers from any mental disorder or condition,‚Äù his lawyer responded. ‚ÄúThus, Mr. Depp‚Äôs mental condition is not ‚Äòin controversy‚Äô nor does good cause exist under the rule for an IME of Mr. Depp. ¬†‚ÄúIt is a preposterous notion that an IME now would shed light on Mr. Depp‚Äôs mental state at the time of Ms. Heard‚Äôs abuse hoax back in 2016. Ms. Heard‚Äôs effort treads a well-worn path of victim blaming using the pretext of mental health. By Ms. Heard‚Äôs tortured credibility logic, current IME‚Äôs would also be warranted for all the dozens of eyewitnesses who have attested to the various facets of the hoaxes they witnessed years ago.‚Äù Share this:

snippet.title: JOHNNY DEPP v AMBER HEARD Trial DELAYED As Judge Sets NEW DATE
snippet.description:
The Johnny Depp v Amber Heard trial in Virginia has been delayed with the judge setting a new date.

Johnny Depp and Amber Heard were fighting over a continuance that now doesn't matter.

Johnny Depp is thanking his fans after his defamation lawsuit against Amber Heard was postponed.

The $50 million defamation lawsuit was delayed on Friday from January 11, 2021, to May 3, 2021, by Circuit Chief Judge Bruce White in Fairfax County, Virginia due to the coronavirus pandemic, according to Deadline.

"Right now, the Virginia Supreme Court has not authorized us to conduct jury trials," White told the attorneys for both Depp and Heard virtually.

The actor, 57, is currently seeking damages against his ex-wife for an op-ed she wrote in The Washington Post claiming to be a domestic violence victim.

Depp shared a video of himself on Friday on Instagram writing at his desk and thanking his fans for their ongoing support.
